says Pillowtown
has until midnight

115
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,755
to surrender its territory.

116
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:59,133
The United Forts of Pillowtown
declines the request.

117
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,009
It's not a request.

118
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:04,096
I'm giving you an "all tomato."
You give me the whole tomato

119
00:05:04,096 --> 00:05:06,681
or else.
Or else what?

120
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:09,309
[♪♪♪]

121
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,644
See you at midnight.

122
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:12,062
Oh, my God.

123
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:16,650
Do people go to classes?

124
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,819
NARRATOR:
<i>The deadline divides</i>
<i>friendships,</i>

125
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:20,654
<i>families, even study groups.</i>

126
00:05:20,654 --> 00:05:22,739
<i>Pierce Hawthorne</i>
<i>takes Troy's side,</i>

127
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:25,575
<i>citing that Abed is weirder</i>
<i>and more foreign.</i>

128
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,577
<i>Shirley Bennett decides</i>
<i>her allegiance</i>

129
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:29,746
<i>in a text message</i>
<i>to her husband.</i>

130
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:31,957
[SHIRLEY READING TEXT MESSAGE]

131
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:42,009
NARRATOR:
<i>Troy appoints Shirley Bennett</i>
<i>as his second-in-command,</i>

132
00:05:42,009 --> 00:05:45,137
<i>at which point</i>
<i>Pierce switches to Abed's side.</i>

133
00:05:45,137 --> 00:05:48,015
There were those who thought
midnight might come and go.

134
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:51,434
Nothing would happen. Heh.
